<H3><A NAME="news">News:</A></H3>
<UL>
  <LI> <b>SCY-QNet</b> is one of five projects funded in the first
  phase of NSF National Quantum Virtual Laboratory
  (NQVL) program (2024--2025). This project is led by Prof. Eden Figueroa/SBU
  Physics in collaboration with SBU/CS, Columbia University, Yale
  University, and Brookhaven National Labs. (<A href="https://news.stonybrook.edu/newsroom/press-release/general/stony-brook-leads-new-program-designed-to-further-build-and-test-quantum-networks/">more...</A>)
  <LI> <b>Quantum Computing and Networks Protocenter</b>, led by
  Prof. Himanshu Gupta, is funded by SBU's Presidential Innovation and
  Excellence Fund (2023--2027). This protocenter focuses on solving
  complex problems related to the design and development of large,
  scalable, and reliable quantum computing systems. (<A href="https://news.stonybrook.edu/university/qist-protocenters-receive-a-piece-of-the-pie-fund/?utm_source=Stony+Brook+News&utm_campaign=3c074fc303-6-20-23&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_f804059a85-3c074fc303-200007139">more...</A>) 
  <LI> <b>Robotic Assistant for Aging in Place</b>, led by
  Prof. Nilanjan Chakraborty/SBU Mech. Engg., is funded by SBU's
  LINCATS Pilot program (2024--2025). This project is to explore the design and use
  of a robotic manipulation system to assist the elderly continue to
  live in their own homes. 
  <LI> <b>Caregiving Robot Assistant (CART)</b>, led by Prof. IV
  Ramakrishnan, is funded by U.S. Army (2023--2027).  This project is to build a
  prototype assistive robotic system and evaluate it in its utility in
  helping patients with ALS and their caregivers.
  (<A href="https://news.stonybrook.edu/university/sbu-research-team-developing-a-robot-to-help-als-patients/">more...</A>)
</UL>
